This paper discusses the Variational Autoencoder (VAE) architecture, which is commonly used in machine learning for representation learning and generative modeling. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the local behavior of the VAE, which is relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also includes theoretical analysis and experiments, which are relevant to neural networks (cs.NE) and statistical learning (cs.SD).
